snippet.textDisplay:
The Packers all year have been this first half team that’s always struggled more all around in the second half. That’s exactly what happened in this playoff game. They were passing the ball all over. Aaron Jones has decent, and their pass rush consistently got to Russell Wilson.

Then the second half comes, and the Packers can’t run the ball, they can’t consistently go through the air, and the defense can’t get stops. The game came down to a one score game at the end. The Seattle offense let a sack happen against a great pass rush, and the defense couldn’t stop Rodger and Adams.

Overall, it was a tale of two halves that came down to the final two possessions. It was the Packers who made the clutch plays on offense and defense. We’ll see if this formula can work against the 49ers next week.

snippet.textDisplay: I know the 49ers are a great team and look like the best team left but I really wanted to see Rodgers vs Brees matchup . i dont recall them ever matching up in the playoffs . but we've got Rodgers vs wilson already . I personally like to see QB matchups and with Brees getting closer to retirement, we only gonna get a few last couple games out of him . I'd love for them to be againts other historical greats , not no Jimmy G or cousins matchup . same with Brady . not taking nothing away from the Titans afterall they earned it , but you would like to see the games historical great QBs face off against each other since they only have a few years left in them if any . it sucks we never got a Brady vs Rodgers or brees Superbowl .  if the 49ers make the Superbowl , Jimmy G doesnt necessarily add any spice to the historical story line , neither does tannahill . at this point the sexiest matchup we could get is Rodgers vs Mahomes . As you can tell , I'm a very QB biased fan . I love great QB matchups .
